	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You will get a hum and some video noise if the power supply is wrong.
<br />Most people dont know what the rating means or how to read them.
<br />Nes uses an AC to 9vAC most systems are ac to dc and around 9v.
<br />Then you have to check dc adapters because they can have different polarities making the center + or -
<br />
<br />I just did a rgb nes for some one and they ran into the hum problem cuz of the wrong power adapter.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


